{
  "stem": "3022.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I would-- I would call it a-- today probably compared to modern-- to modern Orthodox, because all the laws of kashrut and holidays were observed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And-- and boys were required to wear hats, and prayers were said before the school day started, Hebrew prayers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "As I was growing up, I was exposed to a very warm, loving family life.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "My grandmother's house was the center, the hub, of the-- all family activities.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "On Saturday afternoon, her children with the grandchildren would come to the house, and family affairs would be discussed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "My grandmother would tell the children what-- what problems would arise in a family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "If somebody had financial problems, you know, she would seek the help of other-- of her other children.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "If relatives came from out of town from small villages to visit or came to go to [INAUDIBLE], she made sure that they were put up.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "She was very involved in-- in charity.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "She was like the chairlady for a charity organization called [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Gimelat ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Hassid. ?] I remember every Wednesday night, she was out on town, going to her friends, collecting money either for a dowry for a girl who did not have the money or for a widow who was desolate or for orphans.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "We did not have welfare organizations.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "It was-- the welfare was provided by the community itself, by people in the community.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "I remember my mother and my aunt getting together on the evenings playing the mandolin, singing the popular songs.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And I remember playing with my cousins, the children of my mother's sisters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "It-- it was a life that the memories of it return to me occasionally in my dreams.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
